SIMPLE: blubber
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blubber
<hw>Blub"ber</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Blobber</er>, <er>Blob</er>, <er>Bleb</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A bubble.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At his mouth a <qex>blubber</qex> stood of foam.</q>
<rj><qau>Henryson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The fat of whales and other large sea animals from
which oil is obtained. It lies immediately under the skin and over the
muscular flesh.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large sea nettle or
medusa.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blubber</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Blubber
<hw>Blub"ber</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Blubbered</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Blubbering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To weep noisily, or so as to
disfigure the face; to cry in a childish manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She wept, she <qex>blubbered</qex>, and she tore her hair.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blubber</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Blubber
<hw>Blub"ber</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To swell or
disfigure (the face) with weeping; to wet with tears.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Dear Cloe, how <qex>blubbered</qex> is that pretty face!</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To give vent to (tears) or utter (broken words or
cries); -- with <xex>forth</xex> or <xex>out</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blubbered</ent>⟦br⟧
